  "commentary": "With SPX at 6561.7 sitting between the max negative gamma at 6550 (-10.9B) and max positive gamma at 6600 (+3.1B), dealers are currently in buy-the-dip mode as they're short gamma below spot and will amplify any downward moves toward the massive negative GEX walls clustered around 6550-6540. The breakout regime with -52.8B total GEX means dealers will chase momentum in either direction - buying rallies toward 6600 where they flip to selling, or aggressively buying dips if we break below the 6550 support wall.\n\nKey battle zone is 6550-6600 with the gex_surge event suggesting rapid position changes that could trigger violent moves through either boundary, particularly dangerous on a break below 6550 given the amplifying negative gamma cascade waiting below.\n\nBottom line: expect volatile swings between 6550 and 6600 with potential for sharp moves outside this range.",
